registry.title: Public Packages (0x0001-0x7fff)
registry.note:
The IANA will assign a serial number to each package meeting the conditions of registration (except for an update of an existing package, which retains the serial number of the package it is updating), in consecutive order of registration. The serial number will be used to identify the package in the binary-coded version of the Megaco/H.248 protocol. Serial number 0 is reserved. Public packages MUST be given serial numbers in the range 0x0001 to 0x7fff. Private packages MUST be given serial numbers in the range 0x8000 to 0xffff.
For full details on the requirements for package registration see .
IANA will maintain the currency and public availability of the tabulation of public and private packages. Packages will be listed in increasing order of serial number. The latest Package version is entered, replacing the previous version in the registry.

registry.note:
Errors consist of an IANA registered error code and an explanatory string.
When a MG or MGC reports an error to a MGC, it does so in an error descriptor. An error descriptor consists of an error code and optionally the associated explanatory string. The error code and the explanatory string are registered with IANA.
For full details on the requirements for error code registration see .

The ServiceChangeReason parameter specifies the reason why the ServiceChange has or will occur. It consists of an alphanumeric token and, optionally, an explanatory string.
For full details on the requirements for ServiceChange reason registration see .
The following ServiceChangeReasons are defined. The Reference for the below defined ServiceChange Reasons is ITU-T Rec. H.248.8 unless otherwise noted.

record.description: Loss of lower layer connectivity (e.g. downstream sync)

registry.title: Profile Names
registry.note:
Profile names are used by or H.248.1 in the Servicechange request and reply commands. Profiles may be specified to further define how the H.248 protocol is used and what functionality is supported by an MG. The profile itself specifies what options associated with H.248 have been used. For example: transport and packages used for an application.
Profile names shall be in accordance with the registration rule in section 14.4 of H.248.1/Megaco. Profile names shall not exceed 64 characters in length.
For full details on the requirements for profile name registration see .
The IANA shall provide the list of profile names in alphabetic order.
